urgency: 1.28-[OPTIMA]- Please find the below response from AFLS: As we discussed earlier the reason revenue was null for some versions is that there are no corresponding records in booking info and booking rated tables and as explained earlier, it’s an existing behavior. In the last discussion, MIS user requested to check for all other scenarios where Optima is performing partial commits in DB and upon checking we could see that for some of the bookings, the records were available in booking table and were not available in customer table. On further analysis, we could see that there is booking confirmation message coming from CIBER/BA80 with customer information, this is the reason records were not available in customer table for the respective booking and this is another scenario where partial commit is happening. Currently pending with the user to advise 1.27-[OPTIMA]-chaser has been sent to the suppliers 1.25-[OPTIMA]-Currently pending with the suppliers 1.22-[OPTIMA]-Update from AFLS: As mentioned in previous email, we could see the records found in booking & booking_leg tables and not available in customer table. On further analysis could see there are confirm booking we are receiving without customer details from CIBER & BA80 and there no customer details for booking with other airline prefix. Since this is not like a partial comment in DB, its valid scenario, so the only scenario we are facing is loose configuration change. Please find the below sample message from CIBER without customer details. "QK XXXXXXX .YYYYYYY 092000 SSN/1 20JAN2021/1020+060 MWB/N/075-42949082/STN-MAD RTG/MADBCN CMD/CONSOL CACESA ITN/IB1130/20JAN/MADBCN/SS//K6T1MC0.067 SPH/A/IBC USR/001AARS/QLM PRI/999999 " Have asked MIS team to check and advise 1.20-[OPTIMA]-Chaser has been sent to the suppliers 1.15-[OPTIMA]- Update from AFLS : We are working on the list of scenario where Optima create records in booking and booking_leg tables and not creating in other booking related tables. As discussed earlier scenario 1 when do modification in loose configuration screen its partial creating records in some of booking tables. On our future testing we could see records found in booking & booking_leg tables and not available in customer table, we are analyzing the scenario on which this pattern of records. Once after the analyze will let you know whether its valid scenario or not, keep post updates on 20th Jan. 1.8-[OPTIMA]-AFLS to provide an update by 15th Jan 1.7-[OPTIMA] - Chaser has been sent to the suppliers 1.5-[OPTIMA]-AFLS have checked with their BA and internal team for the below and they need to have a code walkthrough to identity all the scenarios, which they need to discuss with architect team and have scheduled call internal tomorrow, once after the call they will share us the ETA. 1.4-[OPTIMA]-We had a meeting and below are the MOMs: Below are the Minutes for the meetings: 1. AFLS mentioned that certain tables (info and rate) are not updated with subsequent versions if loose config is changed. It was also understood that loose config data is not in booking/booking leg hist tables but still they are incremented with versions. IAG IT team has asked AFLS to kindly provide the rationale for change in only subset of tables (and none of them have loose config data). AFLS will discuss this internally and come with answers. 2. IAG IT Team has also asked AFLS on all possible scenarios where related tables are not be updated. With this MIS support and business will have understanding on impact on different fields. 3. AFLS to provide timelines on when they can provide answers to above questions. 12.21-[OPTIMA]-A call will be scheduled on 4th Jan between users/AFLS 12.17-[OPTIMA]-AFLS to provide an update by tomorrow EOD 12.15-[OPTIMA]-AFLS are discussing internally for the next release plan and will let us know the update by Friday EOD. 12.14-[OPTIMA]-chaser has been sent to the suppliers 12,10-[OPTIMA]:Chaser sent to suppliers 12.8-[OPTIMA]:Cha

urgency: [TKT]: Análisis El motivo de que no se actualizara el PNR con el SSR TKNE se debe a que cuando se emitió el billete el 31 de Enero a las 13:38h , la emisión se hizo correctamente pero la actualización del PNR con el número de billete falló. Adjuntamos logs del sistema de esa fecha/hora: Time stamp of record 2020-01-31 1338:13 IN Runid: *12D3M Trx code: SYS500 PID: 125 Date: 20-01-31 Time: 1238:13 QE CT/MAD959 **ERROR EN CREACION DE SSR TKNE** 31JAN20 13:38 SCHEDULE CHANGE IN PROGRESS MKCN1 <SSR TKNE IB HK1 OVDMAD 475 M12JUL 0752100619650C1 /P1 <SSR TKNE IB HK1 MADLHR 3164 M12JUL 0752100619650C2 /P1 <SSR TKNE IB HK1 LHRMAD 3171 O01AUG 0752100619650C3 /P1 <SSR TKNE IB HK1 MADOVD 482 O01AUG 0752100619650C4 /P1 Cómo se ve, en el momento que se crea el elemento SSR TKNE con el número de billete, se produce un error motivado por un 'SCHEDULE CHANGE IN PROGRESS ' Esto hace que la reserva se quede sin billete y RI la cancele. Estos errores se quedan en la cola CT de MAD959, pero desconocemos que equipo toma acción sobre ellos. No, obstante, vemos, que el estado actual de los billetes es REFUNDED por lo que no es necesaria ninguna acción sobre ellos.
